obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (49380)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2022, s. 4, for "New Delhi International Arbitration Centre" (w.e.f. 27-1-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143&sectionId=49380&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) (1) This Act may be called the ^1[India International`
  line `Arbitration Centre] Act, 2019.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be deemed to have come into force on the 2nd March, 2019.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (49381)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2022, s. 5, for "New Delhi International Arbitration Centre" (w.e.f. 27-1-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143&sectionId=49381&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,---`
  line
  line `(a) "Centre" means the ^1[India International Arbitration Centre] established and incorporated`
  line `under section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) "Chairperson" means the Chairperson of the Centre referred to in clause (a) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(c) "Chief Executive Officer" means the Chief Executive Officer appointed under section 21;`
  line
  line `(d) "Committee" means the relevant Committee of the Centre referred to in section 19;`
  line
  line `(e) "Custodian" means the person who is appointed as Custodian under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 11 in respect of the undertakings;`
  line
  line `(f) "Fund" means the Fund of the Centre to be maintained under section 25;`
  line
  line `(g) "Member" means Full-time or Part-time Member of the Centre and includes the`
  line Chairperson;
  line
  line `(h) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(i) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made by the Central Government under this Act;`
  line
  line `(j) "regulations" means regulations made by the Centre under this Act;`
  line
  line `(k) "Society" means the International Centre for Alternative Dispute Resolution, registered as`
  line `such under the Societies Registration Act, 1860 (21 of 1860), and having its registered office at`
  line `New Delhi;`
  line
  line `(l) "specified date" means the date as may be specified by the Central Government by`
  line notification;
  line
  line `(m) "undertakings" means the undertakings of the Society which vests with the Central`
  line `Government under section 7.`
  line
  line `(2) All other words and expressions used herein but not defined and defined in the Arbitration and`
  line `Conciliation Act, 1996 (26 of 1996), shall have the same meanings as assigned to them in that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (49382)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment and incorporation of India International Arbitration Centre`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143&sectionId=49382&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `CHAPTER II`
  line
  line `ESTABLISHMENT AND INCORPORATION OF ^1[INDIA INTERNATIONAL ARBITRATION CENTRE]`
  line
  line `3. Establishment and incorporation of ^2[India International Arbitration Centre].--- (1) The`
  line `Central Government shall, by notification, establish a body to be called the ^2[India International`
  line `Arbitration Centre] for the purposes of exercising the powers and discharging the functions under this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(2) The Centre shall be a body corporate by the name aforesaid, having perpetual succession and a`
  line `common seal with power, subject to the provisions of this Act, to acquire, hold and dispose of`
  line `property, both movable and immovable, and to enter into contract, and shall, by the said name, sue or`
  line `be sued.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2022, s. 6, for Chapter heading "NEW DELHI INTERNATIONAL ARBITRATION CENTRE" (w.e.f. 27-1-`
  line `2023).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for "New Delhi International Arbitration Centre" (w.e.f. 27-1-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (49383)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Declaration of India International Arbitration Centre as an institution of national importance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2022, s. 8, for "New Delhi International Arbitration Centre" (w.e.f. 27-1-2023)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143&sectionId=49383&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `4. Declaration of ^1[India International Arbitration Centre] as an institution of national`
  line `importance.--- (1) Whereas, the objects of the ^1[India International Arbitration Centre] are such as to`
  line `make it as an institution of national importance, it is hereby declared that the ^1[India International`
  line `Arbitration Centre] is an institution of national importance.`
  line
  line `(2) The head office of the Centre shall be at New Delhi and it may with the previous approval of`
  line `the Central Government, establish branches at other places in India and abroad.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (49384)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Composition of Centre.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143&sectionId=49384&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The Centre shall consist of the following Members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a person, who has been a Judge of the Supreme Court or a Judge of a High Court or an`
  line `eminent person, having special knowledge and experience in the conduct or administration of`
  line `arbitration, law or management, appointed by the Central Government in consultation with the`
  line `Chief Justice of India----Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(b) two eminent persons having substantial knowledge and experience in institutional`
  line `arbitration, both domestic and international, appointed by the Central Government----Full-time`
  line `Members or Part-time Members;`
  line
  line `(c) one representative of a recognised body of commerce and industry, chosen on rotational`
  line `basis by the Central Government----Part-time Member;`
  line
  line `(d) Secretary, Department of Legal Affairs, Ministry of Law and Justice or his representative,`
  line `not below the rank of the Joint Secretary----Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) one Financial Adviser nominated by the Department of Expenditure, Ministry of Finance----`
  line `Member, ex officio; and`
  line
  line `(f) Chief Executive Officer----Member, ex officio.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (49385)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Terms and conditions, etc., of Chairperson and Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143&sectionId=49385&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson and`
  line `Members shall hold office for a term of three years from the date on which they enter upon their`
  line `office and shall be eligible for re-appointment:`
  line
  line `Provided that no Chairperson or Member shall hold office as such after he has attained the age of`
  line `seventy years in the case of Chairperson and sixty-seven years in the case of a Member.`
  line
  line `(2) The terms and conditions, salaries and allowances payable to the Chairperson and Full-time`
  line `Member shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The term of office of a Member appointed to fill a casual vacancy shall be for the remainder of`
  line `the term of the Member in whose place he has been appointed.`
  line
  line `(4) The Part-time Member shall be entitled to such travelling and other allowances as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (49386)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Transfer and vesting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143&sectionId=49386&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `On and from the specified date, so much of the undertakings of the`
  line `Society as form part of, or are relatable to the Society, and the right, title and interest of the Society in`
  line `relation to such undertakings, shall, by virtue of this Act, stand transferred to, and vest in, the Central`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (49387)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `General effect of vesting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143&sectionId=49387&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The undertakings vested under section 7 shall be deemed to`
  line `include all assets, rights, leaseholds, powers, authorities and privileges, and all property (movable and`
  line `immovable), including lands, buildings, works, projects, instruments, automobiles and other vehicles,`
  line `cash balances, funds, including reserve funds, investments and book debts of the Society as form part`
  line `of, or are relatable to, the Society and all other rights and interest arising out of such properties as`
  line `were immediately before the commencement of the New Delhi International Arbitration Centre`
  line `Ordinance, 2019 (Ord. 10 of 2019) in the ownership, possession, power or control of the Society, and`
  line `all books of account, registers and all other documents of whatever nature relating thereto.`
  line
  line `(2) All properties and assets as aforesaid which have vested in the Central Government under`
  line `section 7 shall, by force of such vesting, be freed and discharged from any trust, obligation, mortgage,`
  line `charge, lien and all other encumbrances affecting them or of any attachment, injunction, decree or`
  line `order of any court or other authority restricting the use of such properties or assets in any manner or`
  line `appointing any receiver in respect of the whole or any part of such properties or assets shall be`
  line `deemed to have been withdrawn.`
  line
  line `(3) Any licence or other instrument granted to the Society in relation to any undertaking which has`
  line `vested in the Central Government under section 7 at any time before the specified date and in force`
  line `immediately before the specified date, shall continue to be in force on and after such day in`
  line `accordance with its tenor in relation to and for the purpose of such undertaking or where the`
  line `undertaking is directed under section 10, to vest in the Centre, the Centre shall be deemed to be`
  line `substituted in such licence or other instrument as if such licence or other instrument had been granted to the Centre and the Centre shall hold it for the remainder of the period which the Society would`
  line `have held it under the terms thereof.`
  line
  line `(4) If, on the specified date, any suit, appeal or other proceeding, of whatever nature, in relation to`
  line `any property or asset which has vested in the Central Government under section 7, instituted or`
  line `preferred by or against the Society is pending, the same shall not abate, be discontinued or be, in any`
  line `way, prejudicially affected by reason of the transfer of the undertaking of the Society of anything`
  line `contained in this Act, but the suit, appeal or other proceeding may be continued, prosecuted or`
  line `enforced by or against the Central Government or where the undertakings of the Society are directed`
  line `under section 10, to vest in the Centre, by or against the Centre.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (49388)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Liability prior to specified date.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143&sectionId=49388&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Every liability in relation to any undertaking in respect of`
  line `any period prior to the specified date, shall be enforceable against the Society and not against the`
  line `Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (49389)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Power of Central Government to direct vesting of undertaking in Centre.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143&sectionId=49389&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in sections 7 and 8, the Central Government shall, as soon as`
  line `may be after the specified date, direct by notification, that the undertakings and the right, title and`
  line `interest of the Society in relation to such undertakings which had vested in the Central Government`
  line `under section 7, shall, vest in the Centre either on the date of publication of the notification or on such`
  line `earlier or later date as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the right, title and interest of the Society in relation to the undertakings vest, under subsection (1), in the Centre, the Centre shall, on and from the date of such vesting, be deemed to have`
  line `become the owner in relation to such undertakings and the rights and liabilities of the Central`
  line `Government in relation to such undertakings shall, on and from the date of such vesting, be deemed to`
  line `have become, the rights and liabilities, respectively, of the Centre.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (49390)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Management, etc., of undertakings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143&sectionId=49390&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The general superintendence, direction, control`
  line `and management of affairs of the undertakings, the right, the interest in relation to which have vested`
  line `in the Central Government under section 7, shall---`
  line
  line `(a) where a direction has been made by the Central Government under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 10, vest in the Centre; or`
  line
  line `(b) where no such direction has been made by the Central Government, vest in the Custodian`
  line `appointed by the Central Government under sub-section (2),`
  line
  line `and, thereupon, the Centre or the Custodian so appointed, as the case may be, shall be entitled to`
  line `exercise all such powers and do all such things as the Society, is authorised to exercise and do in`
  line `relation to its undertakings.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may appoint any person as the Custodian of the undertakings in`
  line `relation to which no direction has been made by it under sub-section (1) of section 10.`
  line
  line `(3) The Custodian so appointed shall receive such remuneration as the Central Government may`
  line `fix and shall hold office during the pleasure of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (49391)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Duties of persons in charge of management of undertakings to deliver all assets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143&sectionId=49391&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) On`
  line `the vesting of the management of the undertakings in the Centre or on the appointment of a Custodian`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 11, all persons in charge of management of the undertakings`
  line `immediately before such vesting or appointment shall be bound to deliver to the Centre or Custodian,`
  line `as the case may be, all assets, books of account, registers and other documents in their custody`
  line `relating to the undertakings.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may issue such directions as it may deem desirable in the`
  line `circumstances of the case to the Custodian as to the powers and duties of the Custodian and such`
  line `Custodian may also, if it is considered necessary so to do, apply to the Central Government at any`
  line `time for instructions as to the manner in which the management of the undertaking shall be conducted`
  line `or in relation to any other matter arising in the course of such management.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person who on the specified date, has in his possession or under his control, any books,`
  line `documents or other papers relating to the undertakings shall be liable to account for the said books,`
  line `documents or other papers to the Central Government or the Custodian or the Centre, as the case may`
  line `be, and shall deliver them to the Central Government or the Custodian or the Centre or to such person`
  line `or body of persons as the Central Government or the Centre may specify in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government or the Centre may take or cause to be taken, all necessary steps for`
  line `securing possession of all undertakings which have vested in the Central Government or the Centre`
  line `under this Act.`
  line
  line `(5) The Society shall, within such period as the Central Government may allow in this behalf,`
  line `furnish to that Government a complete inventory of all its properties and assets, as on the`
  line `commencement of the New Delhi International Arbitration Centre Ordinance, 2019 (Ord. 10 of 2019)`
  line `pertaining to the undertaking and for this purpose, the Central Government or Custodian or the Centre`
  line `shall afford to the Society, or body all reasonable facilities.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (49392)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Certain powers of Central Government or Centre.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143&sectionId=49392&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government or the`
  line `Custodian or the Centre shall be entitled to receive up to the specified date, to the exclusion of all`
  line `other persons, any money due to the Society in relation to its undertakings which have vested in the`
  line `Central Government or Custodian or the Centre, as the case may be, and realised after the`
  line `commencement of the New Delhi International Arbitration Centre Ordinance, 2019 (Ord. 10 of`
  line `2019.), notwithstanding that the realisation pertains to a period prior to the commencement of the`
  line `New Delhi International Arbitration Centre Ordinance, 2019 (Ord. 10 of 2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (49393)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Objects of Centre.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143&sectionId=49393&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The objects of the Centre shall be,--`
  line
  line `(a) to bring targeted reforms to develop itself as a flagship institution for conducting`
  line `international and domestic arbitration;`
  line
  line `(b) to promote research and study, providing teaching and training, and organising conferences`
  line `and seminars in arbitration, conciliation, mediation and other alternative dispute resolution`
  line matters;
  line
  line `(c) to provide facilities and administrative assistance for conciliation, mediation and arbitral`
  line proceedings;
  line
  line `(d) to maintain panels of accredited arbitrators, conciliators and mediators both at national and`
  line `international level or specialists such as surveyors and investigators;`
  line
  line `(e) to collaborate with other national and international institutions and organisations for`
  line `ensuring credibility of the Centre as a specialised institution in arbitration and conciliation;`
  line
  line `(f) to set up facilities in India and abroad to promote the activities of the Centre;`
  line
  line `(g) to lay down parameters for different modes of alternative dispute resolution mechanisms`
  line `being adopted by the Centre; and`
  line
  line `(h) such other objectives as it may deem fit with the approval of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (49394)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Functions of Centre.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2022, s. 9, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 27-1-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143&sectionId=49394&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Without prejudice to the provisions contained in section 14, the`
  line `Centre shall strive,--`
  line
  line `^1[(a) to facilitate the conduct of conciliation and other forms of alternative dispute resolution`
  line `mechanism, both international and domestic, in the manner as may be specified by the`
  line regulations;]
  line
  line `(b) to provide cost effective and timely services for the conduct of arbitration and conciliation`
  line `at national and international level;`
  line
  line `(c) to promote studies in the field of alternative dispute resolution and related matters, and to`
  line `promote reforms in the system of settlement of disputes;`
  line
  line `(d) to undertake teaching and to provide for diffusion of knowledge of law and procedures on`
  line `alternative dispute resolution and related matters and to award certificates and other academic or`
  line `professional distinction;`
  line
  line `(e) to impart training in alternative dispute resolution and related matters to those who are`
  line `handling arbitration, conciliation and mediation;`
  line
  line `(f) to co-operate with other societies, institutions and organisations, national or international for`
  line `promoting alternative dispute resolution; and`
  line
  line `(g) to perform such other functions as may be entrusted to it by the Central Government for`
  line `promoting alternative dispute resolution.`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (49395)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate proceedings of Centre.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143&sectionId=49395&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceedings of the`
  line `Centre shall be invalid merely by reason of,--`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy or any defect in the constitution of the Centre; or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the appointment of a person acting as a Member of the Centre; or`
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in the procedure of the Centre not affecting the merits of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (49396)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Resignation of Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143&sectionId=49396&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson or the Full-time Member or Part-time Member`
  line `may, by notice in writing, under his hand addressed to the Central Government, resign his office:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chairperson or the Full-time Member shall, unless he is permitted by the Central`
  line `Government to relinquish his office sooner, continue to hold office until the expiry of three months`
  line `from the date of receipt of such notice or until a person duly appointed as his successor enters upon`
  line `his office or until the expiry of his term of office, whichever is the earlier.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (49397)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Removal of Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143&sectionId=49397&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, remove a Member from his`
  line `office if he,--`
  line
  line `(a) is an undischarged insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(b) has engaged at any time (except Part-time Member), during his term of office, in any paid`
  line `employment; or`
  line
  line `(c) has been convicted of an offence which, in the opinion of the Central Government, involves`
  line `moral turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(d) has acquired such financial or other interest as is likely to affect prejudicially his functions`
  line `as a Member; or`
  line
  line `(e) has so abused his position as to render his continuance in office prejudicial to the public`
  line `interest; or`
  line
  line `(f) has become physically or mentally incapable of acting as a Member.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), no Member shall be removed from his`
  line `office on the grounds specified in clauses (d) and (e) of that sub-section unless the Supreme Court, on`
  line `a reference being made to it in this behalf by the Central Government, has, on an inquiry, held by it in`
  line `accordance with such procedure as may be prescribed in this behalf by the Supreme Court, reported`
  line `that the Member, ought on such ground or grounds to be removed.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (49398)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Committees of Centre.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143&sectionId=49398&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Centre may constitute such Committees as may be`
  line `considered necessary to administer various aspects of its functions.`
  line
  line `(2) The composition and functions of the Committees referred to in sub-section (1) shall be such as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Committee shall meet at such time and at such places and shall observe such rules of`
  line `procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings including the quorum as may be`
  line `specified by the regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (49399)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Meetings of Centre.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143&sectionId=49399&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson shall ordinarily preside at the meetings of the`
  line `Centre:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in his absence, the Member chosen by the other Members present amongst`
  line `themselves shall preside at the meetings.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be the duty of the Chairperson to ensure that the decisions taken by the Centre are`
  line implemented.
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson shall exercise such other powers and perform such other duties as are`
  line `assigned to him under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) The Centre shall meet at least four times a year and follow such procedure in its meetings`
  line `including quorum at such meetings in such manner as may be specified by the regulations.`
  line
  line `(5) All questions which come up before any meeting of the Centre shall be--`
  line
  line `(a) decided by a majority of votes by the Members present and voting, and in the event of an`
  line `equality of votes, the Chairperson or in his absence, the person presiding, shall have a casting vote;`
  line
  line `(b) dealt with as expeditiously as possible and the Centre shall dispose of the same within a`
  line `period of sixty days from the date of receipt of the application:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any such application could not be disposed of within the said period of`
  line `sixty days, the Centre shall record its reasons in writing for not disposing of the application within`
  line `that period.`
  line
  line `(6) The Chairperson may invite any expert, not being a Member, to attend the meetings of the`
  line `Centre, but such invitee shall not be entitled to vote at the meeting.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (49400)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Chief Executive Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143&sectionId=49400&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be a Chief Executive Officer of the Centre who`
  line `shall be responsible for day-to-day administration of the Centre and for this purpose, he shall maintain`
  line `liaison with the Centre and the Secretariat.`
  line
  line `(2) The appointment, qualifications and the terms and conditions of services of the Chief`
  line `Executive Officer shall be such as may be specified by the regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chief Executive Officer shall exercise such powers and discharge such functions as may`
  line `be specified by the regulations or as may be delegated to him by the Centre.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (49401)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143&sectionId=49401&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The Centre may, for the purpose of discharging of its powers,`
  line `functions and duties, by general or special order in writing, specify the powers and duties conferred or`
  line `imposed upon the Centre by or under this Act (except the power to make regulation) which may also`
  line `be exercised or performed by the Chief Executive Officer or any officer or officers of the Centre and`
  line `the conditions and restrictions, if any, subject to which the powers and duties may be exercised and`
  line performed.
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (49402)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title Secretariat.
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2022, s. 11, for "Centre" (w.e.f. 27-1-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143&sectionId=49402&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be a Secretariat to the Centre consisting of---`
  line
  line `(a) Registrar, who shall supervise the activities of the ^1[Secretariat];`
  line
  line `(b) Counsel, dealing with the matters relating to domestic and international arbitration; and`
  line
  line `(c) such number of other officers and employees as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The qualifications, experience, method of selection and the functions of the Registrar, Counsel`
  line `and other officers and employees shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (49403)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Grants by Central Government`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143&sectionId=49403&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, after due appropriation`
  line `made by Parliament by law in this behalf, pay to the Centre in each financial year such sums of`
  line `money and in such manner as it may think fit for being utilised for the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (49404)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Fund of Centre.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2022, s. 12, (w.e.f. 27-1-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143&sectionId=49404&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Centre shall maintain a Fund to which shall be credited,---`
  line
  line `(a) all monies provided by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) all fees and other charges received during or in connection with the arbitration, conciliation,`
  line `mediation or other proceedings;`
  line
  line `(c) all monies received by the Centre for the facilities provided by it to the parties;`
  line
  line `(d) all monies received by the Centre in the form of donations, grants, contributions and income`
  line `from other sources; and`
  line
  line `(e) the amount received from the investment income.`
  line
  line `(2) All monies credited to the Fund shall be deposited in such banks or invested in such manner as`
  line `may be decided by the Centre.`
  line
  line `(3) The Fund shall be applied towards meeting the salaries and other allowances of Members,`
  line `^1[Registrar, Counsel and other officers and employees of the Centre] and the expenses of the Centre`
  line `including expenses incurred in the exercise of its powers and discharge of its duties under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (49405)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143&sectionId=49405&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Centre shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant`
  line `records and prepare an annual statement of accounts, including the balance sheet, in such form and`
  line `manner as may be prescribed in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Centre shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor General of India`
  line `and any expenditure incurred by him in connection with such audit shall be payable by the Centre to`
  line `the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any person appointed by him in connection`
  line `with the audit of the accounts of the Centre shall have the same rights, privileges and authority in`
  line `connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India has in connection with`
  line `the audit of the Government accounts, and, in particular, shall have the right to demand the production`
  line `of books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect the offices of`
  line `the Centre.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Centre as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or any`
  line `other person appointed by him in this behalf together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government and the Central Government shall cause the same to be laid`
  line `before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (49406)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Assessment of assets and liabilities of undertaking.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143&sectionId=49406&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `The assets and liabilities in relation to`
  line `any undertaking under this Act shall be caused to be assessed by any agency authorised by the`
  line `Comptroller and Auditor-General of India in such manner as may be specified by him and any`
  line `payment on a claim to be made in relation thereto shall be settled by him between the Society and the`
  line `Central Government and shall be paid by the Society or the Central Government, as the case may be,`
  line `in the manner as may be specified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (49407)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Chamber of Arbitration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2022, s. 13, for "which shall" (w.e.f. 27-1-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143&sectionId=49407&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Centre shall, establish a Chamber of Arbitration ^1[to]`
  line `empanel the Arbitrators and also scrutinise the applications for admission in the panel of reputed`
  line `arbitrators to maintain a permanent panel of arbitrators.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chamber of Arbitration shall consist of experienced arbitration practitioners of repute, at`
  line `national and international level and persons having wide experience in the area of alternative dispute`
  line `resolution and conciliation.`
  line
  line `(3) The Centre shall by regulations lay down the criteria for admission to the panel of the cadre so`
  line `as to maintain a pool of reputed arbitrators having expertise in international commercial arbitration`
  line `and arbitration other than international commercial arbitration.`
  line
  line `(4) The Registrar to the Secretariat of the Centre shall act as the Member-Secretary to the Chamber`
  line `of Arbitration.`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (49408)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Arbitration Academy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143&sectionId=49408&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Centre may establish an Arbitration Academy---`
  line
  line `(a) to train the arbitrators, particularly in the area of international commercial arbitration to`
  line `compete on par with the reputed international arbitral institutions;`
  line
  line `(b) to conduct research in the area of alternative dispute resolution and allied areas; and`
  line
  line `(c) to give suggestions for achieving the objectives of the Act.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of sub-section (1), there may be constituted a permanent three member`
  line `committee in order to suggest and to submit a report to the Centre with respect to the amendments, if`
  line `any, necessary to the rules and regulations made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (49409)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143&sectionId=49409&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, make rules to`
  line `carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `make provision for---`
  line
  line `(a) the terms and conditions and the salaries and allowances payable to the Chairperson and`
  line `Full-time Members under sub-section (2) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(b) the travelling and other allowances payable to the Part-time Members under sub-section (4)`
  line `of section 6;`
  line
  line `(c) the composition and functions of the Committees referred to in sub-section (2) of section`
  line 19;
  line
  line `(d) the number of officers and employees of the Secretariat of the Centre under clause (c) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 23;`
  line
  line `(e) the qualifications, experience, method of selection and the functions of the Registrar,`
  line `Counsel and other officers and employees of the Centre under sub-section (2) of section 23;`
  line
  line `(f) annual statement of accounts, including the balance sheet under sub-section (1) of section`
  line `26; and`
  line
  line `(g) any other matter in respect of which provision is to be made or may be made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (49410)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2022, s. 14, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 27-1-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143&sectionId=49410&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Centre may, with the previous approval of the`
  line `Central Government, by notification, make regulations consistent with this Act and the rules made`
  line `thereunder to provide for all matters for which provision is necessary or expedient for the purposes`
  line `of giving effect to the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such`
  line `regulations may make provision for--`
  line
  line `^1[(a) the manner of the conduct of arbitration and other forms of alternative dispute`
  line `resolution mechanism under clause (a) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(aa) the time and place and the rules of procedure to be observed in regard to the transaction`
  line `of business of the Committee at the meetings including the quorum under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 19;]`
  line
  line `(b) the time and place and rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business of the`
  line `Centre or any Committee including the quorum at the meeting under sub-section (4) of section 20;`
  line
  line `(c) the appointment, qualifications and the terms and conditions of service of the Chief`
  line `Executive Officer under sub-section (2) of section 21;`
  line
  line `(d) the powers and functions of the Chief Executive Officer under sub-section (3) of section 21;`
  line
  line `(e) the criteria for admission to the panel of reputed arbitrators under sub-section (3) of section`
  line `28; and`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter in respect of which provision, in the opinion of the Centre, is necessary for`
  line `the performance of its functions under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (49411)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Laying of rules and regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143&sectionId=49411&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Every rule and regulation made under this Act shall be`
  line `laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for`
  line `a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or`
  line `regulation or both Houses agree that the rule or regulation should not be made, the rule or`
  line `regulation shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case`
  line `may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the`
  line `validity of anything previously done under that rule or regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (49412)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143&sectionId=49412&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal`
  line `proceedings shall lie against the Centre, the Chairperson or Members or its employees and`
  line `arbitrators for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act or the`
  line `rules or regulations made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (49413)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Power to remove difficulty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2022, s. 15, for "two years" (w.e.f. 27-1-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143&sectionId=49413&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions`
  line `of this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such`
  line `provisions, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as may appear to it to be necessary for`
  line `removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made under this section after the expiry of a period of`
  line `^1[five years] from the date of commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before`
  line `each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (49414)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143&sectionId=49414&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00012_A2019-17_1564468638143
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) The New Delhi International Arbitration Centre Ordinance,`
  line `2019 (Ord. 10 of 2019) is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken under the New Delhi`
  line `International Arbitration Centre Ordinance, 2019 (Ord. 10 of 2019), shall be deemed to have been`
  line `done or taken under the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
